      <prefercite id="aspace_d845e3cea468a49ca8a30c532d6c00b1">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Charles Barton Neff Papers. Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_80b6204231f717f929d8036aaf818f01">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Charles Barton Neff graduated from Pomona College in 1954, receiving the degree of B.A. In 1959, he received an M.A. from Yale University and in 1961, he received his Ph.D., also from Yale.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_5d8d21aebe8bb806406a47f5b851e415">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>A collection of questionnaires completed by 320 Americans before and after visits to the Soviet Union in the summer of 1960. These questionnaires were the basis of Charles Barton Neff's doctoral dissertation, "Attitude Change in American Travelers to the Soviet Union" (Yale University, 1961).</p>  
      </scopecontent>
